5. Create `src/persistence/migrations/migration_14_to_15.js` -- extract ALL backfill logic from `deserialize.js` into this file. This is the largest single task. The logic must be copied verbatim, preserving all imports.
6. Test `migration_14_to_15.js` in isolation against saved project fixtures

**Phase C -- Validation layer:**
7. Create `src/persistence/validate.js` -- structural, referential, and value validators
8. Test validators against known-good and known-bad project fixtures

**Phase D -- Wire it all together:**
9. Refactor `src/persistence/deserialize.js` -- replace body with: detect version, run migrations, validate
10. Update `src/persistence/serialize.js` -- add `schemaVersion` to output
11. Update `src/persistence/storage.js` -- add backend validation in `setBackend()`

**Phase E -- Verification:**
12. Manual end-to-end test: create project, save, reload, verify all features work
13. Manual test: import a legacy JSON file (version 14), verify it loads correctly
14. Manual test: hand-edit a JSON file to remove fields, verify validation catches errors
15. Manual test: verify autosave still works (5-second debounce, localStorage)

